The paper deals with the problem of tracking sequentially arriving data vectors that lie in a slowly changing low-dimensional subspace, while being robust to corruption by additive sparse outliers. This problem is relevant in several areas of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), information theory (cs.IT), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper's focus on subspace tracking and outlier detection makes it likely to be classified under these sub-categories.
